# Assumption

Infra repo is checked out into SRC_ROOT (eg., /b/chromium).
Google Appengine SDK is checked out to $SRC_ROOT/google_appengine automatically.

# How to run Findit locally?

From command line, run:
  cd $SRC_ROOT/infra/appengine/findit
  $SRC_ROOT/google_appengine/dev_appserver.py .

Then open http://localhost:8080 for the home page.

# How to run test for Findit?

From command line, run:
  cd $SRC_ROOT/infra
  python test.py test --html-report /tmp/coverage appengine/findit

If a code path branch is not tested and no line number is shown in the command
line output, you could open file:///tmp/coverage/index.html to check.

# How to deploy to appengine?

For testing, deploy to findit-for-waterfall.appspot.com:
  $SRC_ROOT/google_appengine/appcfg.py --oauth2 update -A findit-for-waterfall . --version `git rev-parse  --short HEAD`

For release, make sure you are in a clean branch and deploy to findit-for-me.appspot.com:
  git diff origin/master && git status
  $SRC_ROOT/google_appengine/appcfg.py --oauth2 update -A findit-for-me . --version `git rev-parse  --short HEAD`

To make the new version the default:
1. Go to https://appengine.google.com and select the findit-for-me app.
2. Click on the 'Versions' link on the left navigation menu.
3. Make the new version as default.
